A woman was told by Sydney hotel she couldn't breastfeed in '18s only' area . 
 She was directed to use the 'baby room' instead - the hotel's disabled toilet . 
 In Australia, women have a right to breastfeed in public . 
 The federal Sex Discrimination Act makes it illegal to discriminate against a person on the grounds of breastfeeding . 
 The hotel says it is a child and breastfeeding friendly venue . 
 